"Abstract Assessing and managing information systems risk can be handled using structured techniques and made at least semiquantitative in a valid way. Thus, decisions about information systems (IS) investment (and associated countermeasures) can be made subject to the same risk analysis discipline as other areas of corporate expenditure. This article discusses the use of standard structured analysis techniques to provide modelling support for risk analysis, and introduces structured risk analysis (SRA), a technique originally developed at Hyperion by the authors."
